</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Given a function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> and a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000Y.xml"
addr="erct-000Y"
title="Section-retraction pair">section</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> witnessed by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon \colon  f\circ  g = 1_{B}]]></fr:tex>, we define the <fr:em><fr:strong>coherent remainder</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left ({g,\epsilon }\right )\mathclose {}]]></fr:tex> to be the following sum:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[  \mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{f}\mathopen {}\left ({g,\epsilon }\right )\mathclose {} :\equiv  \mathchoice {\textstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({\eta : g\circ  f \sim  1_{A}}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\textstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({\eta : g\circ  f \sim  1_{A}}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({\eta : g\circ  f \sim  1_{A}}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({\eta : g\circ  f \sim  1_{A}}\right )\mathclose {}}}  \mathsf {act}_{f}\circ  \eta  \sim  \epsilon  \circ  f ]]></fr:tex><fr:p>For any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex>, it is evident that the type of <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000W.xml"
addr="erct-000W"
title="Inverse">inverses</fr:link> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is (up to reassociation) precisely the dependent sum <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathsf {section}\,f}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\textstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathsf {section}\,f}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathsf {section}\,f}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathsf {section}\,f}\right )\mathclose {}}}\mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{f}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
