href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0043.agda">erct-0043.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma \equiv \mathopen {}\left ({g\colon  B\to  A,\epsilon \colon  f\circ  g =1_{B}}\right )\mathclose {}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000Y.xml"
addr="erct-000Y"
title="Section-retraction pair">section</fr:link> of a function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex>. Then the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0041.xml"
addr="erct-0041"
title="The coherent remainder of a section">coherent remainder</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2036</fr:anchor><fr:addr>#224</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-224.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>18</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>erct-0043</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>By <fr:ref
addr="erct-0026"
taxon="Lemma" />, we may argue that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{f}\sigma ]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0025.xml"
addr="erct-0025"
title="Retract">retract</fr:link> of a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link>. We let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> be the following type defined using <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0010.xml"
addr="erct-0010"
title="Path object">path object</fr:link> structure of <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001Q.xml"
addr="erct-001Q"
title="Fiber">fibers</fr:link> given in <fr:ref
addr="erct-001R"
taxon="Example" />:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   \begin {aligned}    P &:\equiv     \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x:A}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x:A}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x:A}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x:A}\right )\mathclose {}}}    \mathopen {}\left ({g\mathopen {}\left ({f x}\right )\mathclose {},\epsilon \mathopen {}\left ({fx}\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}    \cong _{\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,\mathopen {}\left ({fx}\right )\mathclose {}}    \mathopen {}\left ({x,\mathsf {refl}}\right )\mathclose {}    \\    P &\equiv     \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x:A}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x:A}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x:A}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x:A}\right )\mathclose {}}}    \mathchoice {\textstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({p : g\mathopen {}\left ({f x}\right )\mathclose {} = x}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\textstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({p : g\mathopen {}\left ({f x}\right )\mathclose {} = x}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({p : g\mathopen {}\left ({f x}\right )\mathclose {} = x}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({p : g\mathopen {}\left ({f x}\right )\mathclose {} = x}\right )\mathclose {}}}    \epsilon \mathopen {}\left ({fx}\right )\mathclose {} = \mathsf {act}_{f}p\cdot  \mathsf {refl}   \end {aligned}  ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>It is not difficult to show using <fr:ref
addr="erct-0042"
taxon="Definition" /> that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{f}\sigma ]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0025.xml"
addr="erct-0025"
title="Retract">retract</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex>; we will not need the further fact that it is <fr:em>equivalent</fr:em> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Therefore, it remains to show that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link>. Without loss of generality, we may assume that we have some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[h: P]]></fr:tex>. By <fr:ref
addr="erct-001B"
taxon="Corollary" />, we may fix <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex> and prove that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left ({g\mathopen {}\left ({f x}\right )\mathclose {},\epsilon \mathopen {}\left ({fx}\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}\cong _{\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,\mathopen {}\left ({fx}\right )\mathclose {}}\mathopen {}\left ({x,\mathsf {refl}}\right )\mathclose {}]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link>. Of course, this is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0025.xml"
addr="erct-0025"
title="Retract">retract</fr:link> of the identification type <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left ({g\mathopen {}\left ({f x}\right )\mathclose {},\epsilon \mathopen {}\left ({fx}\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}=_{\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,\mathopen {}\left ({fx}\right )\mathclose {}}\mathopen {}\left ({x,\mathsf {refl}}\right )\mathclose {}]]></fr:tex> and so by <fr:ref
addr="erct-0026"
taxon="Lemma" /> it is enough to prove that the latter is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link>. In fact, we will deduce this via <fr:ref
addr="erct-002T"
taxon="Lemma" /> by observing that the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001Q.xml"
